      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC614880f02b87100583a989ec0e3196d2"></a>Refitting the rear sprocket
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8559"> </a>Check the cush drive damper (7) condition and, if necessary, replace them by removing them from the flange.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8561"> </a>Refitting is the reverse of removal.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8563"> </a>Apply the recommended grease to the outer diameter of rear sprocket holder flange (4).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8565"> </a>Fit rear sprocket flange (4) onto rear sprocket (5), engaging cush drive damper pins (7).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8567"> </a>Apply specified threadlocker on the nut thread (8).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8569"> </a>Start nuts on cush drive damper pins threaded end (7).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8571"> </a>Tighten the nuts (8) to a torque of 44 Nm Â± 10%, in a cross pattern.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_031403448.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8576"> </a>Check for wear as described under Section "<a href="80837.html#DUC5181dee02b7910058ae1ae901b54fbd2">Inspection of the final drive</a>".
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8581"> </a>To refit the nut (2), follow the specifications for the wheel fixing nut, in Section "<a href="78614.html#DUC8624a9e02aeb100584d0b8bb6ec21ad2">Refitting the rear wheel</a>".
         </div>
      </div>
